> To determine it yourself, measure the diamater of the stud/bolt, then
> measure the number of threads per a given length (I usually take
> an average).


There's a really handy little tool - I think people call it a "thread pitch
gauge" - it came with my tap and die set. It looks kind of like a set of
feeler guages but with teeth that measure the thread pitch. Takes the guess
work out identifying thread pitch.

